WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.003
Finding Mr. Huang: A Missing Hiker in Taiwan's Mountains Nearly Forgotten

00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:31.965
This is a story about a man who found peace in the mountains.

00:00:32.532 --> 00:00:35.935
He hiked alone exploring the peaks in Taiwan's mountains.

00:00:36.736 --> 00:00:38.972
One day he never came home.

00:00:39.205 --> 00:00:42.375
And for seven weeks almost nobody looked for him.

00:00:43.042 --> 00:00:45.545
This is also a story about people who cared.

00:00:45.745 --> 00:00:48.281
About a Facebook friend who refused to give up.

00:00:48.648 --> 00:00:51.518
About me going into the mountains to find him.

00:00:52.085 --> 00:00:55.321
And about why searching for the missing truly matters.

00:00:55.755 --> 00:00:57.891
Petr: This is weird

00:00:58.725 --> 00:01:02.662
Petr: This is mine ribbon.  What does it do here?
(somebody had to take from Puli area)

00:01:06.266 --> 00:01:09.269
September 27th 2025

00:01:09.402 --> 00:01:12.872
I received a message on Facebook from a woman I didn't know.

00:01:14.073 --> 00:01:17.043
She was asking for help to find a missing hiker.

00:01:17.177 --> 00:01:20.346
Her name was Miss Tsai and she explained the situation.

00:01:20.413 --> 00:01:21.781
Petr: Something there

00:01:24.117 --> 00:01:28.221
A man named Huang Jiong Hong (黃炯宏) had gone missing in the mountains.

00:01:29.055 --> 00:01:31.758
He disappeared on August 26th 2025

00:01:31.858 --> 00:01:34.527
but his car was only found one month later.

00:01:35.128 --> 00:01:37.931
The car was reported by a local resident who noticed

00:01:38.064 --> 00:01:40.733
it had been parked too long in the same spot.

00:01:41.267 --> 00:01:45.171
It was at the parking near trail entry to Defulan Trail (德芙蘭步道口) in Guguan (谷關).

00:01:46.639 --> 00:01:50.176
I asked her the obvious question - Why did nobody search before?

00:01:50.543 --> 00:01:52.545
She explained the difficult situation.

00:01:53.179 --> 00:01:55.315
The family didn't know where he went hiking.

00:01:56.850 --> 00:01:59.719
Petr: It is just label (fallen informational sign)

00:01:59.919 --> 00:02:03.056
Huang lived alone and told nobody about his plans.

00:02:03.456 --> 00:02:05.024
When his car was finally found

00:02:05.091 --> 00:02:08.027
it was already more than a month since he disappeared.

00:02:08.294 --> 00:02:14.033
Any tracks or clues or memories of hikers who might have seen him that day would be long gone.

00:02:15.969 --> 00:02:17.370
Petr: Fu*k

00:02:22.108 --> 00:02:26.813
To find someone in the mountains you must first understand who they are and how they think.

00:02:27.580 --> 00:02:31.050
Huang Jiong Hong (黃炯宏) was a single man in his early 50s.

00:02:31.751 --> 00:02:35.622
He had no wife no children and he lived a quiet solitary life.

00:02:36.756 --> 00:02:39.359
Years ago he had been diagnosed with cancer.

00:02:40.026 --> 00:02:43.163
During that difficult time his wife divorced him and left.

00:02:43.730 --> 00:02:46.199
He survived the cancer and beat the disease.

00:02:46.366 --> 00:02:48.568
But afterwards he was alone.

00:02:49.369 --> 00:02:52.272
That's when he discovered something that changed everything.

00:02:52.972 --> 00:02:54.807
He found the mountains.

00:02:55.875 --> 00:02:58.778
Huang posted often on a big Taiwan Facebook hiking group (肉腳登山隊).

00:02:59.245 --> 00:03:02.515
His posts described trails he explored views from peaks 

00:03:02.615 --> 00:03:06.319
and selfies from the mountains with a cute towel around his neck.

00:03:06.886 --> 00:03:11.257
His posts were simple but full of good vibes and people liked the content.

00:03:11.658 --> 00:03:15.728
They could see a man who had found peace and purpose through mountain hiking.

00:03:29.509 --> 00:03:32.312
The family was understandably worried about the situation.

00:03:32.845 --> 00:03:36.316
They didn't want more people getting hurt while searching the dangerous terrain.

00:03:36.516 --> 00:03:39.919
They were concerned about the financial cost of hiring search teams.

00:03:40.620 --> 00:03:43.189
They didn't know there are many professionals and volunteers

00:03:43.256 --> 00:03:46.859
who search for the missing or help with accidents in Taiwan mountains.

00:03:48.194 --> 00:03:51.564
And slowly they were beginning to accept that he was gone.

00:03:51.898 --> 00:03:54.067
Basically they had given up.

00:03:54.834 --> 00:03:57.737
But Miss Tsai couldn't accept giving up on him.

00:03:57.904 --> 00:04:01.207
She wasn't his girlfriend or even a close friend in real life.

00:04:01.541 --> 00:04:04.277
They were Facebook friends who shared the same passion

00:04:04.377 --> 00:04:05.945
for hiking in the mountains.

00:04:06.112 --> 00:04:09.515
And she felt someone had to care enough to keep searching.

00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:11.251
[watch beeping]

00:04:18.524 --> 00:04:18.758
⚠
ALARM

00:04:18.758 --> 00:04:18.992
⚠⚠
ALARM

00:04:18.992 --> 00:04:19.492
⚠⚠⚠
ALARM

00:04:19.692 --> 00:04:20.460
⚠⚠⚠
ALARM

00:04:20.727 --> 00:04:25.465
(Petr: I was thinking it is earquake warning,
but my Garmin watch Detected Incident)

00:04:26.899 --> 00:04:30.670
When she contacted me I began studying his case carefully.

00:04:30.803 --> 00:04:34.607
I looked through all his Facebook posts to understand his hiking habits.

00:04:37.510 --> 00:04:41.547
I could see he used offline maps and knew how to navigate with GPS.

00:04:42.849 --> 00:04:47.120
He hiked carefully and always started early never planning overnight trips.

00:04:50.189 --> 00:04:52.058
He wasn't a reckless hiker.

00:04:57.430 --> 00:04:59.432
Petr: Hey, It`s coming here (helicopter)

00:05:11.210 --> 00:05:13.579
October 2nd 2025
(today)

00:05:14.847 --> 00:05:17.617
The family had not hired or even asked me to search

00:05:17.717 --> 00:05:19.152
they had basically given up.

00:05:19.585 --> 00:05:21.587
I was also busy with our event preparation

00:05:21.654 --> 00:05:24.657
and with another search for a missing senior near Puli.

00:05:31.798 --> 00:05:33.866
But I decided to go anyway.

00:05:34.367 --> 00:05:36.569
I felt sad for this man who loved the mountains

00:05:36.669 --> 00:05:39.439
but was missing with almost nobody searching for him.

00:05:41.007 --> 00:05:43.576
My initial idea was Dongmao Mountain East Peak (東卯山東峰).

00:05:43.910 --> 00:05:45.712
I went there first to survey the area

00:05:45.778 --> 00:05:48.514
and also went to the deep valley behind the peak.

00:05:52.051 --> 00:05:54.287
I continued to the main peak of Dongmao Mountain (東卯山)

00:05:54.387 --> 00:05:57.090
over a rocky ridge where an accident could happen.

00:06:16.242 --> 00:06:19.312
I looked for any signs of someone falling from the trail

00:06:19.445 --> 00:06:21.013
or any suspicious odor.

00:06:21.914 --> 00:06:25.885
I checked under cliffs and steep sections where accidents typically happen.

00:06:54.347 --> 00:06:58.317
The problem was clear - the search area was simply too huge.

00:06:59.285 --> 00:07:02.855
I couldn't just search randomly through such steep and dangerous terrain.

00:07:05.191 --> 00:07:06.526
I needed more information

00:07:06.592 --> 00:07:09.462
to narrow down where the accident most likely occurred.

00:07:09.695 --> 00:07:12.698
Petr: Oh, Fu*k (the rock is loose)

00:07:17.804 --> 00:07:21.340
I even flew my drone over the landslide areas to get a better view.

00:07:52.405 --> 00:07:53.573
When searching for missing people

00:07:53.606 --> 00:07:57.109
I also need to consider a difficult topic - suicide.

00:07:59.245 --> 00:08:02.515
It's crucial to understand if we're looking for a lost hiker

00:08:02.615 --> 00:08:04.317
or someone who had an accident

00:08:04.383 --> 00:08:07.920
or someone who went to the mountains with different intentions.

00:08:10.356 --> 00:08:13.593
This changes everything about how and where to search.

00:08:15.728 --> 00:08:19.732
From what I learned about Huang's habits and his positive posts about hiking

00:08:19.832 --> 00:08:21.133
this seemed unlikely.

00:08:22.201 --> 00:08:25.838
But I couldn't completely rule it out without more information.

00:08:33.479 --> 00:08:35.314
Then came an important breakthrough. (couple days later)

00:08:36.148 --> 00:08:39.452
Miss Tsai and her brother managed to access Huang's Google account.

00:08:39.886 --> 00:08:42.855
In his search history from August 26th they discovered:

00:08:43.189 --> 00:08:47.093
"東卯山6連峰" - Dongmao Mountain Six Peaks traverse.

00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:52.198
This detail told me everything I needed to know about his intentions that day.

00:08:52.865 --> 00:08:55.601
He didn't just want to hike the main trail to Dongmao Mountain.

00:08:57.403 --> 00:09:00.573
He wanted to visit all peaks the less common directions.

00:09:01.374 --> 00:09:04.744
And it meant he went there to hike not for other reasons.

00:09:10.249 --> 00:09:13.519
I also made a detour to the steep trail of the Southeast Peak (東卯山東南峰).

00:09:13.753 --> 00:09:15.555
But I found nothing that day.

00:09:17.657 --> 00:09:21.761
I asked Miss Tsai if the family could obtain the cell phone tower records.

00:09:22.061 --> 00:09:25.965
This data is very helpful for mountain searches because it can tell us much more

00:09:26.032 --> 00:09:28.401
even if not directly the exact location.

00:09:28.834 --> 00:09:31.871
The police had shared one piece of information with the family:

00:09:32.438 --> 00:09:36.175
The last cell signal was on August 30th at 12:11 PM.

00:09:36.609 --> 00:09:39.612
The last cell tower location was on East Guan Road.

00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:42.815
The signal direction was 230 degrees from that tower. (azimut is usually wrong)

00:09:46.786 --> 00:09:49.055
But I needed more than just the last signal.

00:09:49.522 --> 00:09:52.591
I needed the full timeline of tower connections throughout the day.

00:09:53.326 --> 00:09:55.461
When did Huang arrive at the trailhead?

00:09:55.761 --> 00:09:58.431
When did his phone signal stop moving between towers?

00:09:58.965 --> 00:10:04.804
You see if the cell signal connects to the same tower for many hours without moving it tells us something critical.

00:10:05.404 --> 00:10:07.606
It means an accident has already happened.

00:10:07.740 --> 00:10:10.076
The phone is still turned on and transmitting.

00:10:10.176 --> 00:10:12.378
But the person carrying it can no longer move.

00:10:13.512 --> 00:10:17.249
Unfortunately only the last tower connection was known by this point.

00:10:17.883 --> 00:10:19.452
For me to do a proper analysis

00:10:19.585 --> 00:10:23.389
I would need to see the whole day's data which together with his potential hiking plan

00:10:23.456 --> 00:10:26.058
would help narrow the search area significantly.

00:10:26.826 --> 00:10:31.397
But the case was already old and these detailed records were not available anymore.

00:10:32.965 --> 00:10:36.736
After my first search day the family finally decided to take action.

00:10:39.105 --> 00:10:42.041
Huang's father wanted to hire me to help find his son.

00:10:42.675 --> 00:10:44.844
They wanted him found and brought home.

00:10:46.779 --> 00:10:48.447
Based on all the information I gathered

00:10:48.547 --> 00:10:51.751
I identified three main hot zones to focus the search:

00:10:51.851 --> 00:10:54.887
Zone 1: The ridge area near Defulan Famous Tree (德芙蘭名樹).

00:11:01.527 --> 00:11:04.163
Some hikers had reported an unusual smell in this area

00:11:04.263 --> 00:11:06.432
a few weeks after Huang disappeared.

00:11:07.433 --> 00:11:09.668
I had been in this area on my first search day

00:11:09.769 --> 00:11:11.537
but hadn't gone deep enough.

00:11:12.772 --> 00:11:16.242
Zone 2: The Bei Song He Mountain (北松鶴山) area near the parking space.

00:11:19.779 --> 00:11:23.282
There's a trail marked on maps but in reality there is not any trail

00:11:23.349 --> 00:11:25.384
and only steep and dangerous slope.

00:11:25.885 --> 00:11:29.522
The terrain here was bad enough that a fall could easily be fatal.

00:11:30.356 --> 00:11:34.360
Zone 3: The east side of the trail leading to Dongmao East Peak (東卯山東峰).

00:11:35.094 --> 00:11:38.397
This area had very steep slopes on both sides of the ridge trail.

00:11:38.697 --> 00:11:43.469
The area where only experienced hikers will go when visiting less common peaks.

00:11:44.236 --> 00:11:48.174
By this time other SAR volunteers were planning a search during the next weekend.

00:11:50.810 --> 00:11:53.379
October 11th 2025

00:11:53.913 --> 00:11:56.682
Day 47 since Huang disappeared.

00:11:57.650 --> 00:12:00.786
I woke up very early that morning and drove from Puli.

00:12:01.253 --> 00:12:02.621
I had limited time to search

00:12:02.688 --> 00:12:05.791
because we had appointments scheduled that afternoon.

00:12:06.459 --> 00:12:11.330
I only had about 5 to 6 hours total so I needed to search fast and efficiently.

00:12:13.532 --> 00:12:16.235
Right after arriving I went first to Zone 2 -

00:12:16.335 --> 00:12:18.871
the bad terrain under Bei Song He Mountain.

00:12:23.242 --> 00:12:26.712
I have strong faith though I'm not particularly religious.

00:12:27.179 --> 00:12:29.949
Sometimes I go to church with my wife and kids.

00:12:31.350 --> 00:12:33.619
In past searches where I found missing hikers

00:12:33.686 --> 00:12:36.555
I felt like some higher power was guiding me.

00:12:39.291 --> 00:12:42.528
That morning as I prepared to search the dangerous terrain

00:12:42.595 --> 00:12:44.597
I prayed silently in my heart.

00:12:45.264 --> 00:12:47.366
Please help me find this man today.

00:12:48.601 --> 00:12:52.404
I searched through the very steep and broken terrain but found nothing.

00:12:56.041 --> 00:13:00.112
Then I went up to Zone 1 the ridge near the famous tree.

00:13:03.215 --> 00:13:06.018
Petr: What here is old ribbon?

00:13:06.752 --> 00:13:10.589
I went deeper into the valley under this ridge from both sides.

00:13:11.857 --> 00:13:13.092
While we were searching for Huang

00:13:13.159 --> 00:13:15.928
I kept thinking about what could have prevented this tragedy.

00:13:17.763 --> 00:13:19.365
[stone rumbling]

00:13:20.099 --> 00:13:21.634
If you hike in Taiwan's mountains

00:13:21.700 --> 00:13:25.404
please learn from this case and remember these important safety principles:

00:13:26.205 --> 00:13:28.374
Always start your hike early in the morning.

00:13:28.607 --> 00:13:31.177
This gives you plenty of daylight to complete your hike.

00:13:31.410 --> 00:13:33.946
It also gives you buffer time if something goes wrong

00:13:34.013 --> 00:13:35.681
or takes longer than expected.

00:13:36.115 --> 00:13:38.817
Huang always followed this rule - he never started late.

00:13:39.552 --> 00:13:41.520
Tell someone your specific hiking plan.

00:13:42.021 --> 00:13:46.592
Always let a family member or friend know exactly which mountain you're climbing

00:13:46.625 --> 00:13:48.594
and which trail you're taking.

00:13:49.295 --> 00:13:51.530
Tell them when you expect to return.

00:13:51.797 --> 00:13:55.301
This is the single most important thing that could have changed Huang's story.

00:13:55.534 --> 00:13:56.769
[sniffing]

00:13:56.902 --> 00:13:59.205
Because he lived alone and told nobody

00:13:59.305 --> 00:14:03.876
precious weeks were lost before anyone even knew where to search.

00:14:04.476 --> 00:14:06.846
Always bring essential safety gear with you.

00:14:07.213 --> 00:14:10.816
A waterproof rain jacket definitely helps keep your body temperature stable

00:14:10.983 --> 00:14:13.052
if weather suddenly changes.

00:14:13.385 --> 00:14:14.720
A headlamp is crucial

00:14:14.820 --> 00:14:18.324
because you never know if your hike will take longer than planned.

00:14:18.691 --> 00:14:22.194
Bring extra food and water beyond what you think you need.

00:14:22.494 --> 00:14:23.829
These items don't weigh much

00:14:23.896 --> 00:14:26.599
but they can make the difference in an emergency.

00:14:27.032 --> 00:14:30.669
The suspicious smell reported here actually came from these blossoms

00:14:30.836 --> 00:14:32.304
Taiwan Schima (臺灣木荷).

00:14:37.076 --> 00:14:39.178
Hiker: Hello
Petr: Hello

00:14:41.880 --> 00:14:44.817
Use offline maps (GPS) and know how to navigate.

00:14:45.117 --> 00:14:48.354
Huang did use offline maps and was good at navigation.

00:14:49.021 --> 00:14:52.791
But even the best navigation skills cannot prevent every accident.

00:14:53.192 --> 00:14:55.394
A fall a slip on wet rocks

00:14:55.494 --> 00:14:58.330
or some injury - these can happen to anyone.

00:14:59.064 --> 00:15:02.368
If you do have an accident try to stay in place.

00:15:02.868 --> 00:15:06.939
Hikers should take care of themselves and wait for rescue to arrive.

00:15:07.306 --> 00:15:11.744
Sometimes this means staying in place overnight until help comes.

00:15:17.983 --> 00:15:20.085
[dry branch]

00:15:20.252 --> 00:15:23.289
That's why having someone who knows your plan is so critical

00:15:23.422 --> 00:15:25.791
they will send help when you don't return.

00:15:26.125 --> 00:15:29.528
I flew my drone along the ridge to survey from above.

00:15:29.895 --> 00:15:31.664
Still nothing conclusive.

00:15:31.830 --> 00:15:34.667
Finally I moved down to Zone 3.

00:15:39.571 --> 00:15:41.640
I climbed the west slope up to the ridge

00:15:41.707 --> 00:15:46.078
and then focused on the east side which also matched the phone coverage area.

00:15:48.213 --> 00:15:51.050
The terrain under the ridge was absolutely terrible.

00:15:51.984 --> 00:15:54.753
Extremely steep slopes covered with unstable rocks

00:15:54.853 --> 00:15:57.756
and small creeks cutting through the hillside.

00:15:58.257 --> 00:16:01.927
This was dangerous without ropes even for an experienced searcher.

00:16:02.661 --> 00:16:06.598
I attempted to descend the east slope to check below the ridge line.

00:16:07.199 --> 00:16:10.869
At one point the terrain became so steep and unstable that I stopped.

00:16:12.471 --> 00:16:15.641
I told myself - This is crazy. Turn back now.

00:16:15.741 --> 00:16:18.143
This is not worth risking your own life.

00:16:18.577 --> 00:16:22.114
But something made me continue down just a little bit further.

00:16:22.614 --> 00:16:25.217
Just to check what was below this cliff section.

00:16:25.417 --> 00:16:27.720
Just to be absolutely sure before I leave.

00:16:28.754 --> 00:16:32.591
As I carefully descended I started to smell something unusual.

00:16:33.058 --> 00:16:34.626
Petr: I smell something

00:16:34.760 --> 00:16:36.895
I've found bodies in the mountains before

00:16:36.962 --> 00:16:40.432
and the smell is not always intense like people imagine.

00:16:40.833 --> 00:16:43.235
After 47 days I honestly wasn't sure

00:16:43.268 --> 00:16:46.071
if there would even be any smell left at all.

00:16:46.338 --> 00:16:49.475
I didn't focus too much on the smell but it was there.

00:16:50.542 --> 00:16:51.877
Then I saw something black

00:16:51.977 --> 00:16:54.480
against the ground covered by pine needles.

00:16:56.782 --> 00:16:57.716
A shoe.

00:16:57.850 --> 00:17:00.452
Decathlon brand size 44.

00:17:00.853 --> 00:17:03.322
My hands started shaking as I took a photo.

00:17:03.522 --> 00:17:06.658
I immediately sent it to Commander Lin from the SAR team.

00:17:06.892 --> 00:17:10.028
Does this match what he was wearing? Can you confirm?

00:17:10.562 --> 00:17:12.131
While waiting for his response

00:17:12.197 --> 00:17:14.700
I began searching the near area very carefully.

00:17:15.401 --> 00:17:17.002
That's when I found a hat.

00:17:18.170 --> 00:17:20.906
It was pink - one of his favorite pink visors

00:17:20.973 --> 00:17:24.009
that appeared in so many of his Facebook photos.

00:17:25.644 --> 00:17:28.881
My heart was racing now. This was definitely him.

00:17:29.048 --> 00:17:32.050
 Petr: Here is hat. And there is the shoe.

00:17:34.053 --> 00:17:37.623
I continued climbing down more carefully my mind racing.

00:17:38.891 --> 00:17:42.761
Then I had to descend through a steep ditch filled with loose stones.

00:17:45.030 --> 00:17:46.765
Petr: Fu*k I see second shoe.

00:17:47.466 --> 00:17:49.435
Just below where I found the first shoe

00:17:49.501 --> 00:17:51.370
I discovered the second shoe.

00:17:51.537 --> 00:17:54.073
Petr: One shoe, second shoe.

00:17:55.741 --> 00:17:58.744
Petr: OK, You are helping. You are helping OK! (comforting myself)

00:18:01.280 --> 00:18:04.917
If someone had fallen here they would have tumbled even further down.

00:18:09.254 --> 00:18:13.392
Petr: hat... shoe.. He must be over there

00:18:13.892 --> 00:18:15.461
Petr: here is  obvious slide

00:18:16.028 --> 00:18:17.362
Petr: oh, so deep

00:18:29.475 --> 00:18:33.312
I pushed through the vegetation even though it was difficult to reach.

00:18:34.012 --> 00:18:35.581
Through the dense bushes ahead

00:18:35.647 --> 00:18:38.517
I could see colors that didn't belong in nature.

00:18:38.851 --> 00:18:41.587
Something orange. Something blue.

00:18:41.987 --> 00:18:43.155
Petr: I have him!

00:18:43.722 --> 00:18:44.890
Petr: Over there is orange!

00:18:45.657 --> 00:18:46.825
Petr: ahh

00:18:47.159 --> 00:18:50.295
When I got close enough I could clearly see pieces of clothing.

00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:52.798
Petr: Sorry!

00:18:53.899 --> 00:18:55.067
Petr: But you are back!

00:18:55.167 --> 00:18:56.768
Petr: You will go to family OK!

00:18:57.369 --> 00:18:59.638
And then I saw the skull.

00:19:01.039 --> 00:19:02.274
Petr: Oh my god!

00:19:04.243 --> 00:19:06.245
This was Huang Jiong Hong.

00:19:06.712 --> 00:19:09.481
After 47 days exposed to the mountain environment

00:19:09.548 --> 00:19:12.351
there was almost no flesh remaining on his body.

00:19:13.085 --> 00:19:14.620
Petr: It must be terrible fall.

00:19:14.720 --> 00:19:18.390
Petr: The shoes are 20m there and trail is 50m (80m) at least.

00:19:18.690 --> 00:19:21.493
Just bones and some dried darkened skin.

00:19:21.727 --> 00:19:24.696
I stopped moving and just stood there for a moment.

00:19:24.796 --> 00:19:26.832
Petr: Dear heavenly father (pray)

00:19:27.032 --> 00:19:28.166
Then I prayed again

00:19:28.333 --> 00:19:32.504
this time out loud my voice breaking the silence of the mountains.

00:19:33.138 --> 00:19:35.741
Rest in peace Mr. Huang. You are found now.

00:19:35.841 --> 00:19:38.210
Thank you for letting me find you.

00:19:38.410 --> 00:19:40.445
Petr: in the name of Jesus Christ, Amen

00:19:41.813 --> 00:19:45.150
I immediately reported the exact location to the SAR commander.

00:19:45.450 --> 00:19:49.321
Huang's body was located approximately 80 meters below the ridge level.

00:19:50.322 --> 00:19:54.359
The slope was extremely steep - in some sections nearly vertical.

00:19:55.060 --> 00:19:57.329
I carefully worked my way along the slope

00:19:57.396 --> 00:19:59.298
searching for any possible route.

00:19:59.965 --> 00:20:03.869
How do we bring the SAR team back here to recover his body?

00:20:05.237 --> 00:20:08.240
Eventually I found an old abandoned trail

00:20:08.307 --> 00:20:10.442
that had been used for water pipes.

00:20:10.676 --> 00:20:12.211
Following this overgrown path

00:20:12.277 --> 00:20:15.013
I managed to traverse out to the parking area.

00:20:15.514 --> 00:20:18.250
Commander Lin and some family members were already there

00:20:18.317 --> 00:20:19.851
waiting for more details.

00:20:21.386 --> 00:20:24.489
Meanwhile others came down and I led the team back up

00:20:24.556 --> 00:20:28.327
through the difficult terrain helping them prepare a safe route out.

00:20:28.994 --> 00:20:31.697
Later I examined the location more carefully.

00:20:31.997 --> 00:20:34.466
The fall didn't happen directly from the trail.

00:20:35.567 --> 00:20:38.804
Huang had missed a sharp turn and continued along the ridge

00:20:38.870 --> 00:20:40.539
then fell from there.

00:20:40.973 --> 00:20:43.075
We'll never know if this happened during the day 

00:20:43.108 --> 00:20:46.578
or under stress when it was getting dark in the mountains.

00:20:47.145 --> 00:20:50.215
This reminds me why it's so important to carry a good headlamp

00:20:50.315 --> 00:20:53.518
and plan your route with easier sections at the end.

00:20:54.119 --> 00:20:55.787
I wasn't sure where his phone was

00:20:55.887 --> 00:20:59.124
maybe in the bag or in his pocket or just nearby.

00:20:59.358 --> 00:21:00.392
But it explained

00:21:00.459 --> 00:21:03.562
why the cell tower signal never moved after the accident.

00:21:07.266 --> 00:21:09.101
When we finally reached his location

00:21:09.167 --> 00:21:11.903
some brave SAR members put on their protective gear

00:21:11.970 --> 00:21:13.438
to handle the remains.

00:21:15.173 --> 00:21:18.443
They carefully and respectfully packed his remains into a body bag

00:21:18.644 --> 00:21:21.647
then secured it to a SKED rescue litter.

00:21:29.254 --> 00:21:32.891
This story is about more than just finding someone who was lost.

00:21:34.159 --> 00:21:37.696
It's really about the power of caring when others have given up.

00:21:38.230 --> 00:21:41.933
Miss Tsai never stopped believing that Huang deserved to be found.

00:21:43.001 --> 00:21:44.536
She was just a Facebook friend 

00:21:44.603 --> 00:21:46.805
they had never even hiked together in person.

00:21:47.139 --> 00:21:50.676
They connected years ago through their shared love of the mountains.

00:21:51.109 --> 00:21:53.812
But when everyone else had accepted he was gone

00:21:53.945 --> 00:21:56.114
she refused to give up on him.

00:21:56.581 --> 00:21:58.383
Many volunteers came to help

00:21:58.450 --> 00:22:00.786
once the search was properly organized.

00:22:01.219 --> 00:22:04.323
Strangers helping strangers in the mountains.

00:22:04.956 --> 00:22:07.092
This is the spirit of Taiwan mountain rescue

00:22:07.192 --> 00:22:09.961
people who care about bringing the missing home.

00:22:12.331 --> 00:22:13.932
When I think about Huang Jiong Hong (黃炯宏)

00:22:14.032 --> 00:22:16.968
I feel deep sadness mixed with respect.

00:22:17.169 --> 00:22:19.805
Years ago the cancer diagnosis and the divorce

00:22:19.871 --> 00:22:22.641
when he was at his lowest point left him alone.

00:22:23.909 --> 00:22:26.545
But Huang found something that saved him.

00:22:27.079 --> 00:22:29.815
He found peace through hiking in Taiwan's mountains.

00:22:30.582 --> 00:22:33.652
Sharing photos on Facebook exploring new peaks

00:22:33.785 --> 00:22:35.721
finding simple joy in nature.

00:22:36.455 --> 00:22:40.092
In the end these mountains he loved also took his life.

00:22:40.392 --> 00:22:43.562
But I believe he died doing what made him happy.

00:22:45.230 --> 00:22:49.301
Huang Jiong Hong (黃炯宏) was found on October 11th 2025.

00:22:49.668 --> 00:22:53.538
47 days after he disappeared into the mountains he loved.

00:22:54.072 --> 00:22:56.808
His body was recovered by the brave SAR team members

00:22:56.908 --> 00:22:58.744
and returned to his family.

00:22:59.144 --> 00:23:01.947
His elderly parents his brothers with families

00:23:02.013 --> 00:23:03.849
could finally say goodbye properly.

00:23:04.249 --> 00:23:05.784
Even if you love the mountains

00:23:05.817 --> 00:23:07.953
you should not stay there alone forever.

00:23:08.787 --> 00:23:10.222
And to Huang Jiong Hong (黃炯宏) 

00:23:10.322 --> 00:23:14.226
may you rest in peace in the mountains that brought you so much happiness.

00:23:14.526 --> 00:23:15.994
You are not forgotten.

